sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant APIM as Apigee / APIM<br/>(quota enforcement)
    participant F as front12<br/>(HTTP frontend)
    participant P as Apache Pulsar<br/>(message queue)
    participant B as backend12<br/>(batch processor)
    participant US as Underlying Service<br/>(Routing / Search API)
    participant BS as Azure Blob Storage<br/>(result store)

    C->>APIM: POST /batch/submit (API key, up to 10k items)
    APIM-->>APIM: enforce QPS quota (OnlineRoutingBatch_quotaPerSecond)
    APIM->>F: forward request
    F-->>F: validate request, resolve customer token
    F->>P: publish message (batch ID, customer token, API key)
    F-->>C: 202 Accepted (Location: /batch/{batchId}/status)

    loop Client polling (until result ready)
        C->>APIM: GET /batch/{batchId}/status
        APIM->>F: forward request
        F-->>C: 202 Accepted (still processing)
    end

    P->>B: deliver message (up to 40 concurrent per service)
    activate B
    loop Process each batch item
        B->>APIM: forward item request (client API key)
        APIM-->>APIM: enforce underlying service QPS quota
        APIM->>US: GET /routing or /search (client API key)
        US-->>B: item response
        B-->>B: rate-limit (multi-quota mapping per endpoint type)
    end
    B->>BS: write aggregated result
    B-->>P: ack message
    deactivate B

    C->>APIM: GET /batch/{batchId}/status
    APIM->>F: forward request
    F->>BS: check result exists
    BS-->>F: result present
    F-->>C: 303 See Other (Location: signed blob URL)
    C->>BS: GET signed URL
    BS-->>C: download aggregated result (JSON)
